            <div type="translation">
                <p>Through the providence of God, I, E[uretu]s(?), Elder and Trustee, with my wife and children, renovated the forecourt of the temple with the gifts of god. (Hebrew) Euretus made house of prayer, peace.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Transcription from photo. Line 1-2: Ameling Ε[.../..]Σ. The missing letters in Greek render the dedicator's name, which is supposedly given also at the beginning of the Hebrew segment. The Hebrew appears to read "וארטאס," possibly the Greek name "Euretus." The letter-forms, especially the minscule Δ and the shape of the Β, support dating the inscription to a later date, between the fourth to sixth centuries CE (Ameling). </p></div>
            

